node.text:
🌊 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐥𝐢𝐥 𝐤𝐢𝐝𝐝𝐨 𝐥𝐨𝐯𝐞𝐬 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐨𝐜𝐞𝐚𝐧, 𝙝𝙚 𝙞𝙨 𝙖 𝙥𝙞𝙚𝙘𝙚𝙨 𝙖𝙛𝙩𝙚𝙧 𝙖𝙡𝙡.

Last weekend pueo was playing on the monkey bars at the park, he fell onto his bottom and hit his elbow on the astroturf ground. His elbow was swollen and he had limited mobility in that arm. It wasn’t bruised and it wasn’t broken, so we put it in a sling and contacted our friends at @kauaifarmacytea 💫 We picked up a few of their amazing homegrown products to help him heal and 𝙏𝙃𝙀𝙔 𝙒𝙊𝙍𝙆𝙀𝘿 𝙒𝙊𝙉𝘿𝙀𝙍𝙎!! 

we used:

🌿 𝙘𝙤𝙢𝙛𝙧𝙚𝙮 𝙘𝙖𝙨𝙩
🌿 𝙘𝙤𝙢𝙛𝙧𝙚𝙮 𝙨𝙖𝙡𝙫𝙚
🌿 𝙘𝙤𝙢𝙛𝙧𝙚𝙮 𝙝𝙮𝙙𝙧𝙤𝙨𝙤𝙡

First, We applied the salve and the hydrosol onto his arm, then we made the comfrey cast into a paste and applied it all around his swollen elbow. We wrapped it in gauze and kept it on all night. We used the hydrosol and the salve again in the morning and applied the comfrey cast again for another night — and that did the trick! His arm was back to complete mobility! Last weekend he was in a sling, this weekend he’s snorkeling in the ocean.  I am so grateful for my friends Doug and Genna at the Kaua’i Farmacy for their commitment to growing organic medicine to serve our community. I highly recommend all of their products.

✨ @kauaifarmacytea ✨

breast milk is such a gift. have you ever tried breast milk as an adult? it’s the sweetest milk everrrr ✨🕊 did you know you can put a little breast milk in your babies eye to help with eye irritations, we did it and it worked. i’ve also hear of breast milk curing rashes on babies skin. plus… it’s free and convenient. ✨✨🙏🏾✨✨ grateful for these breastfeeding days — we went 2yrs & 7mo strong 💪🏾
